DESCRIPTION:"Life in the Past Lane" a free genealogy class\, will meet on 
 the 2nd and 4th Saturday afternoons at the Lakeport Library. The class is 
 conducted by the Lake County Genealogical Society \\(LCGS\\)\, is free and
  open to anyone interested in pursuing family history.  \n\n \n\nRose Davi
 dson\, president of the LCGS\, will lead the class\, which will explore an
  array of genealogy topics through class discussions\, presentations\, les
 sons and online webinars. At this first reintroduction meeting there is no
  need to bring anything except maybe a notebook / writing stuff. For more 
 information about the class\, email sleeperseeker@gmail.com. https://www.l
 akecountyca.gov/calendar.aspx?EID=2578
