SUMMARY:Sea Chantey and Songs of the Sea Singalong
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T163000
UID:251218XoIA7eobWUKXDpaXFzbKwA
DESCRIPTION:Please note the change of venue and time from our previous sin
 g-alongs.\\* Avast\, ye saucy sailors! Come brave the perilous waters of P
 oint Reyes and join us for a rollicking good time at Point Reyes National 
 Seashore's Sea Chantey Sing-along at the Ken Patrick Visitor Center. Pleas
 e bring your arsenal of sea chanteys\, any musical instruments you'd like\
 , and a willingness to laugh a lot!  It's so much fun when audience member
 s lead shanties for the rest of us to join in on the chorus\, and leading 
 a song is encouraged! If you'd like to find a song \\(or songs\\) to share
 \, I highly recommend setting one of your online music services to a sea c
 hantey radio station and hear what's out there! Practice lyrics! Teach the
  chorus to our audience at the singalong! Our format is informal\, mellow\
 , and supportive\, so if you've been wanting to push your comfort edge and
  lead a song\, this is a perfect low-pressure opportunity. If you'd rather
  just singalong with the chantey choruses\, that's fine too. We always hav
 e a great time no matter what. This free event is for chantey singers of a
 ll levels. Due to the nature of sea chanteys\, there may be lyrics that ar
 e not appropriate for children. Reservations not required. To be added to 
 the notification email list for future singalong dates\, please email pore
 \\_info@nps.gov For more information\, please visit: nps.gov/pore/planyour
 visit/calendar.htm
LOCATION:Point Reyes National Seashore
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/2336824630085003/2336824636751669/?act
 ive_tab=about
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
