X-SOURCE-URLS:{"North Bay Bohemian": "https://safariwest.com/calendar/safari-west-presents-native-bird-connections/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bohemian
SUMMARY:Safari West Presents! Native Bird Connections
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260314T203000
UID:251216nSz3rJDbMUq7gmuu9jau0A
DESCRIPTION:Conservation Dinner Series: Jenny Papkra from  Native Bird Con
 nections joins us in the elephant room after dinner to give a talk about b
 irds. The conservation dinner series is complimentary to all dinner guests
 . If you want to attend this presentation\, please call our reservations t
 eam at \\(707\\) 566-3667 or \\(800\\) 616-2695 and they can book it for y
 ou. Dinner starts at 7:00 PM.    About the Speaker: Jenny has a Bachelor's
  degree with honors from UC Davis in Environmental Interpretation. She has
  been involved with wildlife since 1988\, first with Lindsay Museum for 13
  years and now with Native Bird Connections for 22 years. Native Bird Conn
 ections is permitted with the State and the Federal Fish and Wildlife Depa
 rtments to conduct educational programs within Northern California. NBC su
 pports 13 non-releasable raptors as educational partners. Jenny maintains 
 the NBC collection\, delivers all of the programs and consults with organi
 zations locally and beyond. She is an advisor for the Peregrine Team and t
 he Kestrel Campaign in the Mt Diablo region Jenny has working experience w
 ith most California native wildlife and over 30 species of raptors. She re
 ceived the William Penn Mott Jr. Environmental Award from the Orinda Assoc
 iation in 2009.
