SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260314T023750Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T160000
SUMMARY:FLASH HIKE - Wittenberg\, Sky\, Woodward Valley\, Coast\, Bear Val
 ley Loop
DESCRIPTION:"SONOMA COUNTY OUTDOORS"\nFLASH HIKE - Bear Valley Trailhead a
 t Point Reyes National Seashore.\n\nThis approximately 13-mile hike will d
 epart promptly at 9:40 AM. We will ascend the Mt. Wittenberg Trail (1\,200
  feet) to the Sky Trail\, and traverse that to the Woodward Valley Trail. 
 We will descend Woodward Valley to the Coast Trail\, then head south to th
 e giant eucalyptus tree at the Kelham Beach Trailhead (8 miles). After lun
 ch\, we will continue south to the Bear Valley\nTrail and return to the Be
 ar Valley Trailhead (5 miles). Elevation gain is approximately 1\,800 feet
 \, most of it in the first two miles while ascending Mt. Wittenberg.\n\nBr
 ing plenty of water\, a lunch if you wish\, and wear sturdy hiking shoes. 
 This hike offers spectacular vistas of Limantour Beach\, Drake's Estero\, 
 and Point Reyes (if the marine layer allows). There may be a few trees dow
 n across the trails...requiring a little scrambling at times.\n\nBinocular
 s and a camera are suggested! Layers are recommended as this Sunday looks 
 as if it will be partly cloudy with temperatures in the high 60's (offerin
 g very comfortable hiking weather).
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-outdoors/events/3137597
 05/
