SUMMARY:Breathless Sparkling Wines "Women’s History Celebration Sundays"
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T140000
UID:260218eE2IqjbmBEWJNoEeXWD9gg
DESCRIPTION:**Breathless Sparkling Wines** is hosting a speaker and lunch
 eon series which will be held **every Sunday in March** at the winery’s 
 tranquil outdoor garden in Healdsburg to honor **Women’s History Month**
 . \n\nThe **“Breathless Women’s History Celebration Sundays”** se
 ries aligns with the **National Women’s History Alliance**’s 2026 the
 me\, “Leading the Change: Women Shaping a Sustainable Future\,” which 
 recognizes women advancing environmental\, economic and social sustainabil
 ity through leadership\, innovation and community impact.\n\nEach Breathle
 ss Wines Sparkling Garden Luncheon will be paired with a featured female s
 peaker whose work reflects the evolving role of women in shaping industrie
 s and communities\, sparkling wines\, and wines paired with a lunch prepar
 ed by **Chef Beryl Adler** of Healdsburg's **Acorn Café.** Visit **Breath
 lessWines.com** for more.
LOCATION:Breathless Wines 
URL:https://breathlesswines.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian, Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"North Bay Bohemian": "https://mareislandartstudios.com/events/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bohemian
SUMMARY:In Her Power
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T160000
UID:260204LDO58J9PgkeEHVpaFOIdVw
DESCRIPTION:In Her Power\n\nA Collaboration by Priscila Soares & JeanCheri
 e\n\nIn Her Power is a group exhibition celebrating women’s presence\, s
 trength\, and creative expression. Anchored by a collaborative\, life-size
  sculptural work by Priscila Soares and JeanCherie\, the exhibition brings
  together works by women artists exploring power as something lived\, embo
 died\, and deeply personal.\n\nAt the heart of the gallery stands a mounta
 in lioness woman — a guardian figure shaped by two artists working toget
 her\, each bringing her own voice\, materials\, and vision. Surrounding th
 is central work\, invited artists contribute pieces that reflect their own
  relationship to power\, resilience\, intuition\, and selfhood.\n\nRather 
 than offering a single definition\, In Her Power invites viewers to witnes
 s many expressions of strength — quiet and fierce\, ancestral and contem
 porary\, individual and shared. It is both a celebration of women artists 
 and an invitation to step into presence\, creativity\, and connection.\n\n
 Opening Reception:\n\nMarch 1\, 12–4pm\n\nGallery Hours:\n\nSundays in M
 arch\, 12–4pm\n\nLocation:\n\nMare Island Art Studios\n\n110 Pintado St.
 \n\nVallejo\, CA
LOCATION:Mare Island Art Studios
URL:https://mareislandartstudios.com/events/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
