SUMMARY:Jerry Hannan Band\, with Amy Hogan opening
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260315T180000
UID:260213GdbQgk_fxkm8g8sHMgLVVg
DESCRIPTION:Jerry Hannan is a Marin-based singer/songwriter who has been p
 erforming regionally for years. Previously with the "Mad Hannans" Band\, a
 nd now as a solo artist or with a cadre of musicians as the Jerry Hannan B
 and. UUP's own Tony Blake will be drumming with the band\, along with two 
 other friends \\(guitar/banjo/dobro and bass\\). Jerry received notoriety 
 for his song "Society" that he wrote with Eddie Vedder \\(Pearl Jam\\) for
  the movie "Into the Wild."\n\nAmy Hogan is a beloved local singer-songwri
 ter\, frequently performing with members of her family. She performed in a
 n earlier UUP concert series\, and we are so happy to welcome her back!\n\
 nHeld in the sanctuary of this historic 1901 downtown Petaluma church\, th
 e Sanctuary Concert Series offers an acoustically excellent space for a li
 stening audience.\n\nDonation: $20\, with all proceeds going to the artist
 s. An additional donation opportunity to support the Sanctuary Coalition o
 f Sonoma County will be available\, and all refreshment sales will benefit
  the organization working to protect our migrant neighbors from abduction 
 and deportation.
LOCATION:Unitarian Universalists of Petaluma
URL:https://www.facebook.com/events/915472667673294/
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian, Press Democrat
END:VEVENT
