DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260316T143000
UID:260216I9lbFvsAWU-yUAtZ-vqHaQ
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the 110th anniversary of the 1915 Panama-Pacific Int
 ernational Exposition\, the spectacular World's Fair that helped San Franc
 isco rise from the ashes of the 1906 earthquake. Join us for a lively look
  at the art\, culture\, and characters of the Expo-and how this landmark e
 vent helped shape the Bay Area's recovery and future. So\, come on down fo
 r the fun! Painter\, speaker\, author\, Linda Loveland Reid holds a B.A. \
 \(cum laude\\)\, in both History and Art History from SSU. A Village Netwo
 rk of Petaluma event.
LOCATION:Petaluma Library
URL:https://events.sonomalibrary.org/event/meet-me-fair-panama-pacific-int
 ernational-expo-1915-artist-and-lecturer-linda-loveland-reid
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
