 \n\nWhat you’ll Create\n\nDiscover the joy of tap dancing in our Beginn
 er Tap Dance class\, designed for children aged 6 to 10 years! This class
  introduces students to the fundamentals of tap dance while fostering rhyt
 hm\, coordination\, and confidence in a fun and supportive environment. Da
 ncers will learn foundational steps such as shuffles\, flaps\, and cramp r
 olls\, building towards simple combinations and routines. Through engaging
  exercises and dynamic music\, students will develop timing\, musicality\,
  and precision. Perfect for beginners or those with some experience\, this
  class encourages creativity and self-expression while building essential 
 dance skills. Step into the world of tap and let the rhythm move you! No p
 rior experience required—just bring your tap shoes and enthusiasm to dan
 ce! Recital on Saturday\, March 21st. More info on recital soon.\n\nRequir
 ed Supply List\n\nTap shoes of any color and style\, Comfortable clothing
  to move in or dance-wear such as leotards\, skirts\, skirted leotards an
 d tights \\(with shoes\\) of any color or style. Please no tutus or pajama
 s in class. Hair pulled off face. Dress in layers as it can go from chill
 y to warm fast! Being dressed and ready for class is part of the experienc
 e and encourages focus and participation. You can find tap shoes at Disco
 unt Dance Supply \, Amazon\, Capezio\, and Bloch and sometimes Target 
 for Kid’s sizes. Any color and style will do. Not necessary for the fir
 st class\, may wear hard soled shoes.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 213\, Dance Stud
 io
