BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"North Bay Bohemian": "https://enrichment.kids/ca/sonoma/tuesday-after-school-create-your-own-storybook-world"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bohemian
SUMMARY:After School - Create Your Own Storybook World!
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T153000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260317T173000
UID:251217NOcB5kgVoUKAFhx8Npse3A
DESCRIPTION:Every Tuesday 3:30 PM – 5:30 PM\n\nPlease see website: Exact
  dates are available on Enrichment.kids. Click the registration links belo
 w.\n\nExperience Level\n\nAll Levels\n\nEvent Category: Kids\n\nAge\\(s\\)
 \n\n7-11\n\n$100 – Monthly Session Cost\n\nChildren will be inspired by 
 a different artist each month and create 3D sculptural worlds from their o
 wn conceptualized 2D drawings.\n\nWhat you’ll do\n\nIn this imaginative\
 , hands-on art class\, young artists will explore the magical worlds of be
 loved artists & illustrators. Each month they will learn about a different
  artist:  Phoebe Wahl \\(January\\)\, Antje Damm \\(February\\)\, Karen 
 Collins \\(March\\)\, Richard Scary \\(April\\)\, and Hayao Miyazaki \\(Ma
 y\\) . Inspired by their playful styles\, students will design and devel
 op their very own characters—deciding where these characters live\, wor
 k\, play\, eat\, and sleep! Students will be working independently as wel
 l as in groups to develop their visual storytelling muscles.  Children wi
 ll create 3D sculptural worlds from their conceptualized 2D drawings. They
  will bring their stories to life using a mix of expressive art materials\
 , including:\n\n watercolor\, paint\, pens\, and collage\n\n recycled 
 and found objects to build unique scenes\n\nTogether\, we will learn:\n\nH
 ow to use watercolor techniques to add color and mood\n\nHow scale hel
 ps characters and environments feel real\n\nThe arc of a story—beginnin
 g\, middle\, and end\n\nHow to build a world using background\, middle gr
 ound\, and foreground\n\nBy the end of the class\, each child will have cr
 eated their own illustrated story scene full of imagination\, personality\
 , and creativity. A perfect class for kids who love drawing\, storytelling
 \, and building new worlds!\n\nPick-up & Drop-off\n\nDrop off at 3:30 PM a
 nd pick up at 5:30 PM Drop-off and pick-up will happen outside Room 116 ea
 ch week. For safety purposes\, we ask that parents come inside to sign the
 ir child in and out after each session. You can view a map of our building
  here.\n\nPick-up Service\n\nWe also offer a free pick-up service for your
  kids if you are unable to drop them off after school. More more informati
 on\, please contact Melissa Agocs at melissa@sonomacommunitycenter.org.\n
 \nMembership has its benefits\n\nAll Silver Memberships and above receive 
 10% off the registration cost for any purchase over $40. Materials fees ar
 e not discounted.\n\nBecome a member today and find community\, connection
 \, and creativity.\n\nLocation\n\nRoom 116
LOCATION:Sonoma Community Center
URL:https://enrichment.kids/ca/sonoma/tuesday-after-school-create-your-own
 -storybook-world
X-SOURCE:North Bay Bohemian
END:VEVENT
