SUMMARY:Quench at Copia: “GOAT”-ed Grapes- Chardonnay Edition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260318T183000
UID:260216rDwc01DqQUy53DJ70OvwWg
DESCRIPTION:CIA at Copia is proud to be the home of the newest wine tastin
 g experience and podcast series\, *Quench at Copia\,* with Master Somme
 lier Andrea Immer Robinson. You will get to be part of a live studio audi
 ence through a guided tasting with special guests from the culinary and w
 ine industries who will join along the way. Each event invites you to 
 learn and connect through exceptional wines\, thoughtful pairings\, and l
 ively conversation.  \n\nWhy does Chardonnay taste so different from pla
 ce to place—and why does limestone matter so much? Find out at a live\, 
 in-person tasting during CIA at Copia’s *Quench at Copia* series led
  by Master Sommelier Andrea Immer Robinson with special guest and legenda
 ry winemaker\, David Ramey. In this experience\, you’ll be focusing o
 n one of the “GOAT”-ed Grapes: Chardonnay! You’ll explore stan
 dout Chardonnay styles side by side\, paired with bites designed to amplif
 y flavor and texture. Expect “aha” moments\, lively conversation\, an
 d great white wine.
LOCATION:CIA at Copia
URL:https://www.ciaatcopia.com/quench-wine-podcast-at-copia/?utm_source=we
 bsite&utm_medium=organic&utm_campaign=quench-at-copia-city-spark
