BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup Sonoma County Go Wild Hikers": "https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/events/313771755/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_sonoma_county_go_wild_hikers
X-SOURCE:Meetup Sonoma County Go Wild Hikers
UID:event_313771755@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260314T023756Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T113000
SUMMARY:Sonoma Valley Hike
DESCRIPTION:Go Wild Hikers\nThis is one of my favorite routes in this park
 . The trails we'll hike will pass through the park's northern boundary and
  offers views of Sonoma Valley and the Mayacamas Range. The property is an
  important piece of the Sonoma Valley Wildlife Corridor\, a collection of 
 protected lands allowing animals safe crossing on the valley floor. There'
 s a dog park right next to the regional park if your pup still has energy 
 to burn.\n\n**Where We Meet/Important Directions**\nSonoma Valley Regional
  Park\n13630 Highway 12\, Glen Ellen\, CA 95442\nGoing East on Hwy 12 towa
 rds Sonoma. **Pay Attention! The park is on the right a quick quarter of a
  mile past the Arnold Drive traffic light.**\nGive yourself plenty of time
  to arrive\, pay park fee and use the restroom. It often takes longer than
  you think.\n\n**The Hike**\nWest Sutton Lake\, Woodland Star\, East Sutto
 n Lake\, Valley of the Moon\, Black Canyon Creek and Cougar trails - A loo
 p hike\nLength - +/-4 miles/6.4 kilometers\nElevation change - +/-500 feet
 /152 meters\nDifficulty - 5 out of 10 - mostly easy\nExposures - 75 % sun/
 25% shade - rocky\, poison oak\, ticks and insects.\nBring plenty of water
 . At least 34 oz./1 liter.\nDogs - Yes\, well behaved dogs on a leash are 
 welcome.\nFacilities at trail head - Dog Park\, Water\, picnic tables and 
 restrooms.\nCost - $5 cash.\nParking - $8 per vehicle or free with Regiona
 l Park pass.\nRemember to wear appropriate hiking shoes\, bring plenty of 
 water for your dog too\, a hat\, snacks & layered clothing.\nPlease Do Not
  Use Any scented products the day of a group hike!\nOf course\, we will al
 l look out for each other but ultimately\, hikers are responsible for thei
 r own safety and well-being during hikes.\n\n**After Hike Coffee/Food**\nL
 es Pascals (French bakery)\n13758 Arnold Dr\, Glen Ellen\, CA 95442\n[(707
 ) 934-8378](https://www.google.com/search?q=french+bakery+glen+ellen&oq=fr
 ench+bakery+Glen+ellen&gs_lcrp=EgZjaHJvbWUqDAgAECMYJxiABBiKBTIMCAAQIxgnGIA
 EGIoFMhAIARAuGK8BGMcBGIAEGI4FMgYIAhBFGEAyCAgDEAAYFhgeMggIBBAAGBYYHjIICAUQA
