 olor": { "type": "THEME_COLOR" }\, "thickness": { "unit": "em"\, "value": 
 0.1 }\, "linecap": "square" } ] Workshop: Integrating watercolor with Chin
 ese ink and oil pastel\, with Dr. QinQin Liu .fe-block-44cc3ef0715bb2dda8e
 b {mix-blend-mode: \; } [ { "type": "highlight"\, "id": "b4413bba-8068-482
 5-bc86-e6a2c46bbe60"\, "shape": "underline"\, "isFront": false\, "isAnimat
 ionEnabled": false\, "animation": "draw"\, "duration": 0.5\, "direction": 
 "right"\, "color": { "type": "THEME_COLOR" }\, "thickness": { "unit": "em"
 \, "value": 0.1 }\, "linecap": "square" } ] Limited to 12 students Saturda
 y March 38\, 2026\, 12:30 pm -3:30pm Tickets: $90 for Non-members\; $80 fo
 r members and students Class materials are not included. If you prefer the
  instructor provide your materials\, you have the option of paying an addi
 tional $30 (up until 10 days before the class).&nbsp\; In this lively work
 shop\, Dr. Liu will teach students a unique form of watercolor integration
  with Chinese ink and oil pastel. Students will also learn design\, compos
 ition\, shape\, line\, point\, value and color by painting natural objects
 . By using Chinese brush stroke and wet-on-wet techniques\, participants w
 ill explore the power of positive and negative paintings. They will also e
 xperiment with watercolor expression and abstraction with splashing\, drip
 ping\, and Chinese calligraphy painting.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; The workshop will b
 egin with an instructor demo\, followed by individual instruction and grou
 p discussion Dr. Qinqin Liu has taught watercolor workshops since 2017 at 
 Yosemite National Park\, Sitka Art and Ecology Center\, and Chalk Hill Art
  Residency in California and Oregon Coast. She has practiced ink painting 
 and calligraphy in China since 1974. When she came to the U.S.\, she studi
 ed with award-winning watercolorists Frank Webb and Professor Cheng-Khee C
 hee.&nbsp\;&nbsp\; Required Materials List:&nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp
 \; Sketchbook (at least 5"x 8") ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercolor paper
  (Arches Cold press 140lb at least two sheets 11x15) ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nb
 sp\; 2 B and 6B pencils&nbsp\;&nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Palette fo
 r color mixing (e.g. a recycled egg plastic container) ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &
 nbsp\; Watercolor brushes (Princeton brand is good): Rounds sizes 6 and 10
  or 12\; Flats sizes 1 ½” and larger ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Watercol
 or paints: 3 primary colors (e.g.\, Ultramarine Blue\, Azo Yellow\, and Ca
 dmium Red or rose madder)\, optional sap green\, and any of your favorite 
 colors. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Two water containers (e.g.\, two empty y
 ogurt containers). ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Paper clamps\, a water spray 
 bottle\, sponges\, and a paper towel. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Masking ta
 pes and boards to secure the watercolor papers during the painting. ·&nbs
 p\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Mr. Clean Erasers (cleaning pads that you can buy in W
 almart or other stores). ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Optional: masks\; your 
 favorite natural objects and drawings. Materials Provided by Instructor: 
 ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Chinese ink and brush as well as oil pastels for
  class demo and limited uses. ·&nbsp\; &nbsp\; &nbsp\; Tissue paper\, pla
 stic wraps\, and natural objects such as sunflowers&nbsp\; ·&nbsp\; &nbsp
 \; &nbsp\; Watercolor paintings and sketch examples as well as class hando
 uts.&nbsp\; .fe-block-yui_3_17_2_1_1773314704731_17565 {mix-blend-mode: \;
  } Get Your Ticket Here #block-yui_3_17_2_1_1773314704731_32131 {--sqs-blo
 ck-content-flex: 0\; }
