BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Cool Petaluma": "https://coolpetaluma.org/events/book-club-hope-in-the-dark"}
X-SOURCE-ID:cool_petaluma
SUMMARY:Book Club - Hope in the Dark
DTSTART;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T013000Z
DTEND;TZID=UTC;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260408T030000Z
UID:e5ebc1dd2b090bb477388e2097ef8cd3@coolpetaluma.org
DESCRIPTION:Cool Petaluma Book Club Our book for April\, Hope in the Dark 
 by Rebecca Solnit\, shows us why we should not give up hope\, even though 
 our future is uncertain. In fact\, we should be committed to it in all its
  unknowability. PLEASE NOTE: There are 5 copies at Copperfield’s\; ask f
 or one at the counter. Let them know you’re with the Cool Petaluma Clima
 te Book Club. Plus\, get 10% off! .fe-block-48fda9e02d14584b80b1 {mix-blen
 d-mode: \; } RSVP Here #block-41ef93226c8a0444c843 {--sqs-block-content-fl
 ex: 0\; } Hope in the Dark Solnit’s book is a manifesto for hope in plac
 e of the despair that engulfs many activists when their campaigns to make 
 the world a better place or safeguard local values from globalized corpora
 tions do not bear immediate fruit. Solnit advocates for embracing the dark
 ness of an uncertain future and campaigning from the perspective that prev
 iously unforeseen changes are always possible. In this book\, she seeks to
  safeguard against the cultural amnesia in which people forget that previo
 usly unthinkable events changed history\, such as obtaining suffrage for w
 omen after millennia of patriarchy. In addition\, she emphasizes that no e
 asy cause-and-effect relationship exists between activism and seeing chang
 es realized. Instead\, the path to change twists and turns\, with many def
 eats as well as small victories. .fe-block-5ce66d8084f2469abf99 {mix-blend
 -mode: \; } &nbsp\; [ { "id": "04388466-7135-4ccc-9916-e993de72b63e" } ] G
 et your copy &amp\; start reading: Petaluma Library GoodReads Copperfield
 ’s Books - Tell them you are with the Cool Petaluma Book Club for 10% di
 scount! #block-3fc3e09189c20756044f{ box-sizing: border-box\;height: 100%\
 ;}#block-3fc3e09189c20756044f .sqs-html-content {padding: 6% 6% 6% 6%\;}#b
 lock-3fc3e09189c20756044f {border-radius: 0px 0px 0px 0px\;}.fe-block-3fc3
 e09189c20756044f {mix-blend-mode: \; } &nbsp\;
LOCATION:Crooked Goat Brewing\, 110 Howard Street\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952
URL:https://coolpetaluma.org/events/book-club-hope-in-the-dark
X-SOURCE:Cool Petaluma
END:VEVENT
