X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Meetup: Rebel Craft Collective": "https://www.meetup.com/the-rebel-craft-collective/events/313260336/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_rebel_craft
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Rebel Craft Collective
UID:event_313260336@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260309T023556Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T193000
SUMMARY:Happy Hour Crafts
DESCRIPTION:The Rebel Craft Collective\nWine + tasty snacks + your latest 
 project and a friendly group of likeminded crafters... what better way to 
 unwind? Come join us!\n\nThis is a relaxed\, drop-in-friendly event. Come 
 when you can\, leave when you must. Newcomers and occasional-comers are al
 ways welcome!\n\n**What do we mean by “crafts”?**\nWhatever “craft
 ” means to you! And whatever is portable enough to bring to a wine bar. 
 Knitting\, crochet\, and other fiber arts are most common\, but we have al
 so warmly welcomed people who sketch\, color\, embroider\, bead\, and more
 . If your craft isn’t portable\, we will happily ooh and aah over photos
  of your work-in-progress\, or chat about your plans for your next project
 .\n\n**Health & Safety**\nMasks are very welcome\, and nobody will pressur
 e you to eat or drink. If the weather is nice\, we will try to sit outside
 . If you aren’t eating/drinking during the event\, please consider order
 ing some of La Dolce Vita’s delicious food to-go\, in order to help supp
 ort our gracious\, long-time venue.\n\n**Parking**\nParking in downtown Pe
 taluma is free\, but street parking has a strictly enforced 2 hour limit u
 ntil 6pm. To park for longer\, try the nearest garage:\n\n* The Second Str
 eet Garage entrance is located on C Street between First and Second Street
 s. It's all day parking on every level and a short walk to La Dolce Vita.\
 n\n**Ages**\nIt's a wine bar\, so this event is for adult crafters (though
  you're certainly not required to drink wine!). We’re okay with babes-in
 -arms if you are\, but this is not the right setting for wee crafters who 
 are moving about on their own.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/the-rebel-craft-collective/events/313
 260336/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260208T041705Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260208T041705Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"The Big Easy": "https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/fernando-fidanza-italian-folk-for-the-sound-of-california/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:bigeasy
X-SOURCE:The Big Easy
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260409T230000
DTSTAMP:20260308T185710
CREATED:20260305T172240Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260305T172240Z
UID:10002568-1775764800-1775775600@bigeasypetaluma.com
SUMMARY:Fernando Fidanza - Italian folk for "The Sound of California"
DESCRIPTION:“The Sound of California”\, a tribute to the art\, the culture\, the history\, the folklore and the cuisine of your beautiful state.\nThe project will become a book\, a documentary\, a Youtube and Instagram channel.\nFernando Fidanza\, born in Rome in 1976\, started to play guitar when he was 8 years old \, with his brother’s electric guitar\, inspired by U2. At 12\, in 1988\, the encounter that changed his life. He discovered heavy metal\, mostly with three albums\, …And Justice For All by Metallica\, South Of Heaven by Slayer and Live After Death by Iron Maiden. From that moment guitar and music became his passions\, his dreams\, his life. Thanks to his parents’ mindset he grew up believing that travels and art are the most beautiful and important things in life. He travelled a lot with his music\, and now\, in collaboration with his brother Luca\, has decided to discover The Sound of The World. So he changes country every two or three months\, playing his songs and writing books and shoooting documentaries about the countries he visits and the people he meets. Now\, it is California’s turn.\nIf you want to follow my journey\, here is my Instagram: resonance_thesoundof
URL:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/event/fernando-fidanza-italian-folk-for-the-sound-of-california/
LOCATION:The Big Easy\, 128 American Alley\, Petaluma\, CA\, 94952\, United States
CATEGORIES:Folk
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://bigeasypetaluma.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/IMG_4335-scaled.png
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Mystic Theatre": "https://wl.seetickets.us/event/ben-roy/676995?afflky=MysticTheatre"}
X-SOURCE-ID:mystic_theatre
SUMMARY:Ben Roy
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T200000
DTEND;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260409T230000
