SUMMARY:Grandma Gatewood's Walk by Ben Montgomery
DESCRIPTION:Petaluma Book (And Brew) Club\nGrandma Gatewood\, as the repor
 ters called her\, became the first woman to hike the entire Appalachian Tr
 ail alone\, as well as the first person—man or woman—to walk it twice 
 and three times. Gatewood became a hiking celebrity and appeared on TV and
  in the pages of Sports Illustrated. The public attention she brought to t
 he little-known footpath was unprecedented. Her vocal criticism of the lou
 sy\, difficult stretches led to bolstered maintenance\, and very likely sa
 ved the trail from extinction.\n\nIf you are an audio book or an e-reader 
 this book is on Hoopla.
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/petaluma-book-and-brew-club/events/31
 3746893/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260311T185231Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260311T185231Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
